

# ==== Emojis ====
# ---- General ----
# ✨  :sparkles:                  Add partial new features
# 👍  :+1:                        Update features
# 🎉  :tada:                      Add significant new features
# 🚀  :rocket:                    Update performance
# ⚗  :alembic:                   Experimenting new things
# ♻️  :recycle:                   Refactoring code
# ---- UI/UX ----
# 💄  :lipstick:                  Add or update UI and style files
# 🎨  :art:                       Significant update UI
# 💫  :dizzy:                     Improving UX
# 👾  :space_invader:             Update about animetion
# ---- DB ----
# 🗃  :card_file_box:             Update model shcema
# 🗄  :file_cabinet:              Update about database
# ---- Setting ----
# 🔧  :wrench:                    Changing configuration files
# 📦  :package:                   Updating compiled files or packages
# 🌐  :globe_with_meridians:      Internationalization and localization
# 💡  :bulb:                      Documenting source code
# ---- Remove/Rename ----
# 🗑️  :wastebasket:               Remove file
# 🚚  :truck:                     Move/rename files or repository
# ---- Git ----
# ⏪  :rewind:                    Reverting changes
# 🔀  :twisted_rightwards_arrows: Merging branches
# ---- Fix ----
# 🐛  :bug:                       Fixing a bug
# 🚑  :ambulance:                 Critical hotfix
# ✏️  :pencil2:                   Fixing typos
# 🚧  :construction:              Work in progress
# 💩  :hankey:                    Writing bad code that needs to be improved
# ---- Document, Snapshot etc ----
# 📝  :memo:                      Writing docs
# 🙈  :see_no_evil:               Add or update a .gitignore file
# 📸  :camera_flash:              Add or update snapshots
# 🗂️  :card_index_dividers:        Add or update assets
# ---- Test ----
# ✅  :white_check_mark:          Adding a test
# 💚  :green_heart:               Fixing Test or CI Build
# ---- Analytics, Log ----
# 📈  :chart_with_upwards_trend:  Analytics or tracking code
# 🔊  :loud_sound:                Adding logs
# 🔇  :mute:                      Removing logs
# ---- App ----
# 🐳  :whale:                     Work about Docker
# 🔥  :fire:                      Work about Firebase
# ---- Security ----
# 🔒  :lock:                      Fixing security issues
# 👮  :cop:                       Update security features
# ---- OS ----
# 🍎  :apple:                     Fixing something on macOS
# 🐧  :penguin:                   Fixing something on Linux
# 🏁  :checkered_flag:            Fixing something on Windows
# 🍏  :green_apple:               Fixing something on iOS
# 🤖  :robot:                     Fixing something on Android.
# ---- Dependencies ----
# ⬇️  :arrow_down:                Downgrading dependencies
# ⬆️  :arrow_up:                  Upgrading dependencies

# ==== Format ====
# :emoji: Subject
#
# Commit body...

# ==== The Seven Rules ====
# 1. Separate subject from body with a blank line
# 2. Limit the subject line to 50 characters
# 3. Capitalize the subject line
# 4. Do not end the subject line with a period
# 5. Use the imperative mood in the subject line
# 6. Wrap the body at 72 characters
# 7. Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
#
# How to Write a Git Commit Message http://chris.beams.io/posts/git-commit/

# for http://memo.goodpatch.co/2016/07/beautiful-commits-with-emojis/
